trans-unit.source: The ActiveDirectoryAccessRule class is used to represent an access control entry (ACE) in the discretionary access control list (DACL) of an Active Directory Domain Services object.
trans-unit.target: Klassen ActiveDirectoryAccessRule brukes til å representere en access control oppføring (TILGANGSKONTROLLISTEN) i detaljert tilgangskontrollisten (DACL) til et Active Directory Domain Services-objekt.

trans-unit.source: The ActiveDirectoryAccessRule class contains properties of the access rule such as the trustee, access control type, access mask, and inheritance flags.
trans-unit.target: Klassen ActiveDirectoryAccessRule inneholder egenskaper for tilgangsregelen som trustee, tilgang kontrolltypen, maske og arveflagg.

trans-unit.source: This type of access rule is set on an <xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity> object.
trans-unit.target: Denne typen tilgangsregel er angitt for en <xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity>objektet.</xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity>

trans-unit.source: After the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity> object is committed to the directory store, it will modify the security descriptor of the object according to the rules set on the ActiveDirectoryAccessRule object.
trans-unit.target: Etter den <xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity>objektet er skrevet til mappen lageret, den endrer sikkerhetsbeskrivelsen for objektet i samsvar med reglene som er angitt for objektet ActiveDirectoryAccessRule.</xref:System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectorySecurity>
